SENATE BILL 183
E4 6lr1550
SB 5/20 – EHE (PRE–FILED)
By: Senator Hester
Requested: October 31, 2025
Introduced and read first time: January 14, 2026
Assigned to: Education, Energy, and the Environment
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Safety – Maryland Cyber Reserve – Established
3 FOR the purpose of establishing the Maryland Cyber Reserve within the Military
4 Department to provide educational and technical support to prevent and resolve
5 certain cyber attacks; and generally relating to the Maryland Cyber Reserve.
6 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
7 Article – Public Safety
8 Section 13–101, 13–203(b), 13–206(a), and 13–210
9 Annotated Code of Maryland
10 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
11 BY adding to
12 Article – Public Safety
13 Section 13–5A–01 through 13–5A–08 to be under the new subtitle “Subtitle 5A.
14 Maryland Cyber Reserve”
15 Annotated Code of Maryland
16 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
17 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
18 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
19 Article – Public Safety
20 13–101.
21 (a) In this title the following words have the meanings indicated.
22 (b) “Department” means the Military Department.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
